<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Two British girls have been hospitalised after they were allegedly gang raped following a party while on holiday in Italy.</p>

<p>The teens remain in hospital after they were punched and kicked by a group of boys, in the small town of Marconia in the southern region of Basilicata.</p>

<p>The tourists, whose ages have not been revealed, were attending a house party on the edge of town when they were attacked.</p>

<p>It is not clear if the alleged rape took place at the event itself or somewhere nearby.</p>

<p>The 12,000 residents of Marconia are in deep state of shock, according to the local paper which called it an 'extremely shameful' case (pictured: the main street in the little town)</p>

<p>The girls were able to make it back to their accommodation where police were alerted and they were then rushed to a hospital in Matera, around 40 miles away.</p>

<p>The 12,000 residents of Marconia are in deep state of shock, according to local paper La Gazetta Del Mezzogiorno which called it an 'extremely shameful' case.</p>

<p>The Pisticci State Police Commissioner is leading the investigation and few details have been released due to young ages of the alleged victims.</p>
